             deposed, he lost one half pint pewter pot out of his tap room, that he found it in the coat pocket of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said, to be sure I did the thing, I have no witnesses to my character here now, I little thought of coming here, I was told I was clear at Hicks's-hall.</p>
               <p>The court enquired his age, it appeared he was upwards of seventy, the jury recommended him to the mercy of the court.</p>
